    ANGULAR

    Basic buliding Blocks

    1)Module - To import 3rd party modules(root module)
    2)Component - To create html,css and ts file

    Basic commmands

    1)ng new project_name- To create a new project
    2) ng g c Component_name - To create a new Component
    3) ng serve --open - To run angular file

    Basic Concepts

 1)Data Binding - Share data b/w components

    ts---> component
    html---> view

    a) One way data binding (1 direction)
        ts-> html or html-> ts

        a.1) Component to view

            i)String interpolation (1 direction) - {{expression}}
            ii)Property binding -[attribute_name] ="property"

        a.2)View to component

            i)event binding (1direction ) - (event_name) ="function_name()"
            ii)event binding using $event (event_name)= "function_name($event)"
            iii)event binding using template reference variable - #variable_name

    b) Two way data binding (Two direction) - ts--> html, html-->ts

            i)ngModel - FormsModule in app.module.ts - [(ngModel)]= "proprty_name"      


 2) Angular Routing

    to set path for a component
    {
        path:"value" , component:class_name
    }

    eg: login

    {
        path: '', component: LoginComponent   
    }

3) Dependency Injection

To share data b/w two dependend classes-

    constructor (private router:Router)
    eg: Router class- navigateBYUrl is used to navigate the Component_name

4)Angular Services

    to hold redundant data
    ng g s sevice_name

5)Angular directives - To manipulate DOM

    a)Component Directives(array)
    b)Structural Directives(table)
        1) *ngFor=""
        2) *ngIf=""


6)Angular FormsModule
    a)Template Driven Forms (first design html page and cant do validation)
    b)Model driven Forms(first design model in its file, easy validation mthds)
     - Advanced Validation
     1)Reactive Forms
     from group,aray,control
     we can directly add validations via importing Reactive form module

7)Local Storage
    a)setItem - To store data
    b)getItem - To recieve data
    c)removeItem - To remove data
        


8)Parent child communication

    parent-> child
    child->parent

    eg:
        Dashboard -> parent
        delete -> child

9) Angular pipes






        
    
